        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 10:29PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 1029 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northeast of Birch River, or 8 miles southeast of Sutton,
moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sutton, Gassaway, Birch River, Flatwoods, Little Birch, Centralia,
and Erbacon.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 79 between mile markers 55 and 68.
Route 19 between mile markers 59 and 68.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
